cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance analysis of a network infrastructure for communication systems, specifically cloud radio access network (C-RAN), which involves distributed antenna systems (DASs). This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to communication systems, networking, and information theory. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper uses random matrix theory to analyze the performance of C-RANs. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a new network infrastructure to enhance network coverage and save energy. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the separation of radio front ends from baseband units and their distributive location in physical positions. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on multimedia specifically, but it does discuss the performance of communication systems.
